And if ſometimes Good Men are left to their own Precipitance, as Joſiah, when he was not


to be diſſwaded from Attacking Pharaoh-Necho; 
               2 Chron. 25. 20.and Wicked Men are left to their own Perverſeneſs and Obſtinacy, as Pharaoh; or to their Pride, as Iſa. 10.the Haughty Aſſyrian; and they periſh in it: This in the Voluntary World is no more extraordinary, than when there is Seed-time and Harveſt in the Natural World; that is, that each acts according to the Nature they are of, and the Condition they are in.
